text.div: **test From Nwas111 - No Action Required - Please Disregard Test

<content styleCode="bold">Pathways Disposition: Dx09</content> <br/> <content>For Persistent Or Recurrent Symptoms: Get In Touch With A Local Service For A Non-urgent Appointment</content> <br/> <br/> <content styleCode="bold">Consultation Summary:</content> <br/> <content>Illness - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <content>Warm to touch</content> <br/> <content>Head lice</content> <br/> <content>Head lice contact</content> <br/> <content>Recent sudden loss of clumps of hair</content> <br/> <br/> <content styleCode="bold">Pathways Assessment:</content> <br/> <content>An injury or health problem was the reason for the contact.</content> <br/> <content>User comment - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <content>Heavy bleeding had not occurred in the previous 2 hours.</content> <br/> <content>An illness or health problem was the main problem.</content> <br/> <content>User comment - '**Test From NWAS111 - No Action required - Please Disregard Test case**'</content> <br/> <content>The individual was not fighting for breath.</content> <br/> <content>The main reason for the assessment was not an allergic reaction, heart attack, chest/upper back pain, probable stroke, recent fit/seizure or suicide attempt.</content> <br/> <content>The main reason for contact was not new confusion, declared diabetic hypo/hyperglycaemia, or ICD shock.</content> <br/> <content>The skin on the torso felt normal, warm or hot.</content> <br/> <content>Pathway selected - Skin Problems</content> <br/> <content>The main problem was not a rash, itch, jaundice, skin lumps or abnormal bruising.</content> <br/> <content>The main problem was head lice.</content> <br/> <content>There had been contact with somebody with head lice.</content> <br/> <content>There was recent patchy hair loss.</content> <br/> <content>User comment - 'GP - Spencer Street Surgery - Cumbria (Home GP)'</content> <br/> <br/> <content styleCode="bold">Advice Given:</content> <br/> <content>Head lice is common. Speak to a pharmacist for advice on suitable treatments.</content> <br/> <br/>
